definitions.definition: The dignity and ecclesiastic office of Roman Catholic cardinal .
examples: The cardinalate ranks equal to a secular prince of the blood.

definitions.definition: The Roman Catholic cardinals, taken collectively .
examples: The cardinalate under a maximum age composes the conclave which elects the pope.

main_definition: The dignity and ecclesiastic office of Roman Catholic cardinal .
secondary_definitions: The Roman Catholic cardinals, taken collectively .
